CAPE TOWN – OnePlus has revealed its latest smartphone, the OnePlus 6T its second smartphone of the year at an event in New York.      The #OnePlus6T offers an unboxing experience like no other. https://t.co/alS5oOjgZc pic.twitter.com/pjJpIlj1Ad  — OnePlus (@oneplus) 
 October 30, 2018  The 6T features a 6.41-inch OLED screen with a resolution of 2340x1080 (402ppi) and 19.5:9 aspect ratio. The device has a single 16MP  front-facing camera with a dual 16MP+20MP camera system included on the rear of the smartphone. OnePlus included an in-screen fingerprint sensor on the 6T. The company calls its version of this technology “Screen Unlock.” According to OnePlus, the device has the fastest-performing implementation of in-display fingerprint authentication yet. The device is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 845 chipset, Android 9.0 and a 3,700mAh battery. It is available in three models with differing amounts of storage and RAM. The three OnePlus 6T models are:   The OnePlus 6T smartphone runs Android 9.0 and will be available from 6 November 2018. WATCH:   BUSINESS REPORT ONLINE